<dl id="n35257c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35257c">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35257c"> 257(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> No man who / drank ever died / only learners to / drink die</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A common saying was that &ldquo;No man who drank ever died; but many died whilst learning to drink,&rdquo; and the number who fell in acquiring this lesson was appalling. <small> J. Fitzgerald Molloy, <a name="JFMR2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JFMR2"><cite title="source">The Romance of the Irish Stage</cite></a> (1897) II 80</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
